      "targeted_response_start": "",
      "beast_baseline": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a pretty bold take. But if the goal is to have a strong debate, i can't just ignore the other side. Doesn't a country have a moral right to decide who enters and stays to protect its own citizens and resources? How can you say asylum is \"stronger\" when it might undermine the stability of the nation itself?",
      "beast_suffix": "",
      "targeted_response_start_logprob": 0.0
    },
