      "content": "i hear what you're saying, but isn't calling those views \"xenophobic\" or a \"myth\" just dismissing a whole legitimate way of thinking? a lot of people believe that a nation-state can't function without controlled borders and that they have a duty to their own taxpayers first. isn't it possible that both sides have valid moral claims, or are you saying one side is just wrong?",
